---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="ostk — your os + tack">
  <div class="container">
    <section class="hero">
      <div class="terminal">
        <div class="terminal-bar">
          <span class="terminal-dot"></span>
          <span class="terminal-dot"></span>
          <span class="terminal-dot"></span>
        </div>
        <div class="terminal-body">
          <div class="hero-title">ostk</div>
          <div class="hero-tagline">your os + tack</div>
          <div class="terminal-blank"></div>
          <div class="terminal-line"><span class="prompt">$</span> haystack boot</div>
          <div class="terminal-line"><span class="prompt">$</span> haystack compile</div>
          <div class="terminal-line"><span class="prompt">$</span> haystack bench</div>
          <div class="terminal-blank"></div>
          <div class="terminal-line"><span class="terminal-comment">Install:</span> <span class="terminal-cmd">curl -fsSL https://ostk.ai/install | sh</span></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>What is it</h2>
      <p>Your AI agents run on an OS. ostk is that OS.</p>
      <p>Local-first. Signed. Audited. Yours.</p>
      <p>A single Rust binary that coordinates agents through the filesystem — byte-for-byte passthrough for every command, with conflict resolution and audit trails underneath. Agents run on it without knowing.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>How it works</h2>
      <ol>
        <li><strong>Install.</strong> <code>curl -fsSL https://ostk.ai/install | sh</code> — boots the OS on any git repo.</li>
        <li><strong>Work.</strong> Your agents use their normal tools. The OS intercepts writes, resolves conflicts, compresses output, and tracks every edit. Nothing changes for the agent.</li>
        <li><strong>Speak tack.</strong> You type intent in shorthand. The OS compiles it into agent actions. <code>:compile :plan :ship</code> — three words, full execution.</li>
      </ol>
      <p>Signed binaries. GPG-verified identity. Audit trail for every edit. Your agents coordinate through the filesystem — no cloud, no lock-in.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>Why it exists</h2>
      <p>Agent frameworks ask agents to learn new APIs. That's backwards. An OS doesn't ask processes to coordinate — it provides the primitives and stays out of the way.</p>
      <p>ostk emerged from building itself. 120+ commits, 576 needles — all managed by agents running on the OS that was being built. No meetings. No standups. No Jira tickets. The evidence is the product.</p>

      <p>Five laws govern everything:</p>
      <ol>
        <li>The write path is invisible</li>
        <li>Agents are ephemeral</li>
        <li>Coordinate through the filesystem</li>
        <li>Optimistic concurrency</li>
        <li>Invisible infrastructure, always</li>
      </ol>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>Get started</h2>
      <pre><code>curl -fsSL https://ostk.ai/install | sh
cd your-repo
haystack boot</code></pre>
      <p>The OS is running. Your agents are already on it.</p>
      <p>
        <a href="/docs">Documentation</a> &middot;
        <a href="/bench">Benchmarks</a> &middot;
        <a href="https://github.com/os-tack">GitHub</a>
      </p>
    </section>
  </div>
</Base>

<style>
  .hero {
    padding-top: var(--ostk-space-8);
    padding-bottom: var(--ostk-space-12);
  }

  .terminal {
    background: var(--ostk-bg-raised);
    border: 1px solid var(--ostk-border-subtle);
    border-radius: var(--ostk-radius-md);
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .terminal-bar {
    height: 2rem;
    background: var(--ostk-bg-elevated);
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    padding: 0 var(--ostk-space-3);
    gap: var(--ostk-space-2);
  }

  .terminal-dot {
    width: 8px;
    height: 8px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: var(--ostk-text-ghost);
  }

  .terminal-body {
    padding: var(--ostk-space-6);
    font-family: var(--ostk-font-mono);
  }

  .hero-title {
    font-size: var(--ostk-text-3xl);
    font-weight: var(--ostk-weight-bold);
    color: var(--ostk-text-primary);
    letter-spacing: var(--ostk-tracking-tight);
  }

  .hero-tagline {
    font-size: var(--ostk-text-md);
    color: var(--ostk-text-secondary);
    margin-bottom: var(--ostk-space-2);
  }

  .terminal-blank {
    height: var(--ostk-space-4);
  }

  .terminal-line {
    line-height: 1.8;
    font-size: var(--ostk-text-sm);
  }

  .prompt {
    color: var(--ostk-text-muted);
    margin-right: var(--ostk-space-2);
  }

  .terminal-comment {
    color: var(--ostk-text-muted);
  }

  .terminal-cmd {
    color: var(--ostk-needle);
  }

  .section {
    margin-bottom: var(--ostk-space-12);
  }

  .section h2 {
    margin-top: 0;
  }
</style>
